<p>Design tokens are the visual <strong>design atoms</strong> of the design system â€“ specifically, they are named entities that store visual design attributes. We use them in place of hard-coded values (such as <code>hsl</code> values for color or <code>rem</code> values for spacing) in order to maintain a scalable and consistent visual system for UI development.</p>

<p>Those visual design atoms are centralized and propagated as tokens to any project, designer or developer adopting the system, as easy-to-use, predictable JSON files, structured by scope category: <a href="https://gitlab.com/katapult-magazin/katapult-design-system/-/blob/master/src/design-tokens">tokens.json</a></p>

<p>Most of the following design tokens are available by default in the <code>kds.css</code> as CSS custom property. To access these CSS variables, append a double dash to the token key. For example: <code>var(--space-m)</code> gives you acces to use the <code>space-m</code> spacing unit, resulting in <code>1rem</code>.</p>

{% for scopeName, scopeProperties in site.tokens %}
  <h3 class="text-normal mt-xl">{{ scopeProperties.meta.title }}</h3>
  <p>{{ scopeProperties.meta.description | safe }}</p>
  <table class="table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Token property</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for key, data in scopeProperties.props %}
        {% set colorPreview = '' %}

        {% if string.startsWith(data.value, 'hsl') or string.startsWith(data.value, '#') %}
          {% set colorPreviewProperty = ' --color-preview: ' + data.value + ';' %}
        {% endif %}

        <tr>
          <td><code>{{ scopeProperties.meta.infix + '-' + key }}</code></td>
          <td><code style="color: var(--color-text);{{ colorPreviewProperty }}">{{ data.value }}</code></td>
        </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
{% endfor %}
